 border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 18px; font-family: Roboto, &quot;helvetica neue&quot;, -apple-system, system-ui, &quot;system-ui&quot;, &quot;segoe ui&quot;, Oxygen-Sans, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); text-align: start;"></p><p style="margin-bottom: 31px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 18px; font-family: Roboto, &quot;helvetica neue&quot;, -apple-system, system-ui, &quot;system-ui&quot;, &quot;segoe ui&quot;, Oxygen-Sans, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); text-align: start;"></p></div></div><div data-label="Row" data-key="row" data-atomgroup="row" id="r-1657094583320" class="gf_row" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1657094583320" data-extraclass=""><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-12 gf_col-md-12 gf_col-sm-12 gf_col-xs-12" id="c-1657094583441" data-id="1657094583441"><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1657030716163" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1657030716163"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p><strong>There is no straightforward answer on how many protein shakes a day to consume because it depends on such factors as body weight, activities, and protein intake from other sources. While an average person can benefit from 1-2 shakes per day, experienced athletes may require more. Thus, fitness goals and training schedules must be considered to determine protein intake.</strong></p></div></div></div></div><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1656944560008" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1656944560008" data-resolution="3000x3000"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs gf-elm-center-lg" data-exc=""><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/41807db8-df0f-4c77-ac7b-9ef2a5b867c0/-/format/auto/-/preview/3000x3000/-/quality/lighter/Shakers-with-Protein.jpg" alt=" How Many Protein Shakes a Day You Need" class="gf_image" data-gemlang="en" width="1200" height="800" data-width="100%" data-height="auto" title=" How Many Protein Shakes a Day You Need" natural-width="1200" natural-height="800"></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1655318077242" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1655318077242"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h2 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Benefits of Whey Protein and Other Shakes</h2></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1657165631372" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1657165631372"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>When it comes to protein shakes, the options are endless! From whey to casein, soy to pea, and even <a href="https://torokhtiy.com/blogs/reviews/best-hemp-protein-powders" class="">hemp</a>, each type has its unique perks. So, what are the general benefits of these delicious drinks? Let's take a look!</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1677176311291" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1677176311291"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Increased Muscle Mass</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1677176308221" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1677176308221"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>If you're looking to build some serious muscle, whey protein is your new best friend! This powerful protein is loaded with essential amino acids that your muscles need to grow and repair. By sipping on whey protein shakes after your workouts, you can speed up muscle recovery and kickstart new muscle growth. <a href="https://www.healthline.com/nutrition/10-health-benefits-of-whey-protein#TOC_TITLE_HDR_2" class="" target="_blank">Whey protein is one of the most complete sources of protein available</a>.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1672252301355" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1672252301355"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><b>Promotes Weight Loss and Maintenance</b></h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1673148837602" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1673148837602"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Whey protein and other protein shakes are particularly <a href="https://clinicalnutritionespen.com/article/S2405-4577(22)00285-6/fulltext" class="" target="_blank">effective aid for weight loss</a> and maintenance. Whey helps to reduce appetite and increase feelings of fullness and satisfaction, making it easier to stick to a healthy eating plan. By replacing high-calorie snacks or meals with whey or other protein shakes, you can better manage your calorie intake and achieve your weight loss goals.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1673148955371" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1673148955371"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><b>Boost Strength and Athletic Performance</b></h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1672877429601" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1672877429601"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Protein shakes don't just help to increase muscle mass - they can also give your strength and athleticism a serious boost! That's because protein is essential for building new muscle tissue, as well as repairing and maintaining existing muscle. By fueling your body with the protein it needs, you can enhance your strength and performance during workouts and other physical activities. Moreover, studies have shown that whey protein can help increase muscle size and strength more effectively than other types of protein supplements.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1673150972295" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1673150972295" data-resolution="3000x3000"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs gf-elm-center-lg" data-exc=""><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/bf4bde78-1e0a-4b07-bea2-d7b1278cae8a/-/format/auto/-/preview/3000x3000/-/quality/lighter/Making-Clean.jpg" alt="Athlet Performing Clean" class="gf_image" data-gemlang="en" width="1200" height="800" data-width="100%" data-height="auto" title="Athlet Performing Clean" natural-width="1200" natural-height="800"></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1682488725268" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1682488725268"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><b>Quicker Recovery and Soothing Muscle Soreness</b></h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1675008595469" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1675008595469"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>One of the great perks of protein shakes is their ability to speed up recovery. More so, studies show that <a href="https://www.verywellfit.com/whey-protein-powder-nutrition-and-health-benefits-5193649" class="" target="_blank">whey protein</a> is considered vital for muscle growth and repair, especially when compared to soy and <a href="https://torokhtiy.com/blogs/reviews/best-casein-protein-powder" class="" target="_blank">casein protein</a>, its high-level of branched-chain amino acids (BCAAs) also makes it a popular choice for muscle recovery post-workout.</p><p>While scientific evidence on whether protein supplements can reduce lingering soreness is inconsistent, <a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/24435468/" class="" target="_blank">studies have demonstrated their benefits for post-exercise muscle anabolism</a>, which may facilitate the recovery of muscle function and performance and reduce muscle soreness and damage, particularly in situations where you are not consuming enough protein or are in a caloric deficit.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1677092026768" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1677092026768"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><b>Convenient and Easy to Digest</b></h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1682488729715" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1682488729715"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Protein shakes are not only a convenient option for people with busy lifestyles, but they're also easy to digest. If you're someone who struggles to digest whole foods, protein shakes can be a great alternative as they are typically easier to absorb. Plus, they're a quick and effective way to supplement your diet and improve your health and fitness. So, whether you're on the go or simply looking for a hassle-free option, protein shakes are a fantastic choice.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1673148974101" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1673148974101"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h2 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><b>How Many Protein Shakes Can You Consume Per Day?</b></h2></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1682490165739" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1682490165739"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>While protein shakes can be a convenient and effective way to supplement your diet, it's important to understand the appropriate amount to consume per day that will suit your fitness goal without causing any negative side effects. So, even such a simple question like is it bad to drink 2 protein shakes a day or is two protein shakes a day too much cannot get a straightforward answer. The amount of protein shakes you can consume per day depends on a few different factors:</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1682490198769" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1682490198769"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><b>Your Daily Protein Requirements</b></h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1682490215078" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1682490215078"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>For most exercising individuals who are maintaining or building muscle mass, protein needs are <a href="https://jissn.biomedcentral.com/articles/10.1186/s12970-017-0177-8" class="" target="_blank">1.4-2 g</a> per 1 kg of body weight (or ~0.64-0.91 g of protein per 1 lb of body weight).</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1682491702223" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1682491702223" data-resolution="3000x3000"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs gf-elm-center-lg" data-exc=""><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/00542f1a-b67a-4336-91c3-e483b352a7f7/-/format/auto/-/preview/3000x3000/-/quality/lighter/Deadlifting-at-the-Gym.jpg" alt="WBCM Deadlifting" class="gf_image" data-gemlang="en" data-width="100%" data-height="auto" title="WBCM Deadlifting" width="1200" height="800" natural-width="1200" natural-height="800"></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1682490199197" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1682490199197"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><b>Your Overall Diet</b></h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1682490215427" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1682490215427"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Another factor to consider is your overall diet. If you're consuming enough protein from other sources such as meat, fish, eggs, and dairy products, you may not need to supplement your diet with protein shakes as frequently. However, if you're following a vegetarian or vegan diet, or if you have difficulty consuming enough protein from whole foods, protein shakes can be a convenient and effective way to meet your daily protein requirements.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1682490198573" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1682490198573"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><b>Your Goals</b></h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1682490214769" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1682490214769"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Thinking of how often should you drink a protein shake?  The answer to this question lies in your goal. For example, if your goal is to build muscle mass, you may need to consume more protein to support muscle growth and repair. In this case, you may benefit from consuming multiple protein shakes a day. On the other hand, if you intend to lose weight, you may need to consume fewer protein shakes to avoid calorie surplus. Most experts recommend taking protein shake twice a day and limiting it to 3 per day to leave enough variety of protein foods in your diet. Some suggest splitting your protein intake into four doses per day without exceeding the daily recommended volume of protein powder.&nbsp;</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1682528408646" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1682528408646" data-resolution="3000x3000"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs gf-elm-center-lg" data-exc=""><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/db867ea3-4c67-44a6-ae6f-6cd73d1687c4/-/format/auto/-/preview/3000x3000/-/quality/lighter/Squat-With-Bar.jpg" alt="WBCM Squatting With Bar" class="gf_image" data-gemlang="en" data-width="100%" data-height="auto" title="WBCM Squatting With Bar" width="1200" height="800" natural-width="1200" natural-height="800"></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1682490160096" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1682490160096"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h2 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><b>How Many Protein Shakes a Day to Lose Weight?</b></h2></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1672877436078" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1672877436078"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Protein shakes can be beneficial during weight loss, as reducing calorie intake is important and a high protein diet is recommended. Protein shakes are often low in calories and high in protein, making them a convenient and effective way to increase protein intake while reducing overall calorie intake. So If you're looking to shed some pounds, you may have considered adding protein shakes to your diet but how many should you have each day to maximize weight loss? Well, there is no direct answer to this but we will have got you covered with some advice.</p><p>Can you drink more than one protein shake a day to lose weight? We recommend that you should start with one protein shake a day and evaluate the impact on nutrient balance, calorie intake, comfort, and appetite. If you decide that more shakes fit well into your diet, go for it.While protein shakes won't magically make you lose weight, they can be a helpful addition to your overall plan.</p><p>A study shows that women who followed a high-protein diet for 14 weeks lost 1.7 times more body fat than those on a high-carb diet. And in a 12-week study, women with a normal weight but high body fat percentage lost an additional 3 pounds of body fat and around 1 inch in waist circumference on a high protein diet. This means a high protein diet can help to lose weight.</p><p>Since there's no direct answer to this question, individuals need to consider their goals and go for what suits them best.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Liquid" data-key="liquid" data-atomgroup="module" id="m-1673150613840" class="module-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-liquid" data-ver="1.1" data-id="1673150613840" data-name="Right click on this, and choose Edit Code."><div class="module gf_module- gf_module--lg gf_module--md gf_module--sm gf_module--xs {{extraClass}}"><!-- Begin Mailchimp Signup Form --><style>.evg-mail-form h3 {margin-top: 0;}.evg-mail-form {margin: 50px 0;border-radius: 7px;border: 1px solid #bbbbbb;padding: 22px;padding-right: 50px;position: relative;font-family: Montserrat,sans-serif;}.evg-mail-form__grid {display: grid;grid-template-columns: 200px 1fr;align-items: center;gap: 50px;}.evg-mail-form__image {max-width: 100%;border-radius: 7px;}.evg-mail-form__inputs {display: grid;grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr 1fr;gap: 15px 10px;}.evg-mail-form__inputs #mce-responses {grid-column: 1/4;}.evg-mail-form__inputs input {width: 100%;box-sizing: border-box;font-size: 17px;padding: 10px 10px;border: 1px solid #bbb;outline: none;box-shadow: none;background-color: white;font-weight: 400;font-family: Montserrat,sans-serif;}.evg-mail-form__inputs input.mce_inline_error {border-color: red !important;}.evg-mail-form__inputs input[type="submit"] {text-transform: uppercase;background-color: #ef0404;color: white;border: none;outline: none;box-shadow: none;cursor: pointer;font-weight: 700;border-radius: 5px;font-family: Montserrat,sans-serif;}.ev